<p>A possible solution to the “boundary problem” (how is it that we are not all just one bound experience? why are we separate moments of experience?) is that the thing that creates a boundary around an individual’s experience is a topological pocket, and within it, there is a field.</p>



<p>The question then arises, what does it feel like to be that field in the topological pocket?</p>



